<section class="hero about-hero">
  <div class="hero-content">
    <h1>🎬 About <span class="brand">After the Credits</span></h1>
    <p class="lead">Your digital film community for reviews, ratings, and discovery.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="about-main-bg">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-section">
      <h2>What is this?</h2>
      <p>After the Credits is a modern web app for film lovers to discover, rate, and discuss movies. Built for SFSU's CSC317, it demonstrates:</p>
      <ul class="feature-list">
        <li>📝 User registration and login</li>
        <li>🔒 Secure session management</li>
        <li>🔑 Password hashing</li>
        <li>🎥 Movie database integration</li>
        <li>🛡️ CSRF protection</li>
        <li>✅ Form validation</li>
        <li>🔐 Protected routes</li>
      </ul>
      <p>This project is for educational purposes and showcases best practices in web development.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tech-stack">
      <h2>Technology Stack</h2>
      <ul class="feature-list">
        <li><strong>Backend:</strong> Node.js, Express.js</li>
        <li><strong>Database:</strong> MongoDB with Mongoose ODM</li>
        <li><strong>Frontend:</strong> HTML, CSS, JavaScript (Vanilla)</li>
        <li><strong>Template Engine:</strong> EJS</li>
        <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> bcrypt, express-session</li>
        <li><strong>Security:</strong> csurf for CSRF protection</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

